<p>Steve is the founder and director of Dynamix and has been a performer, dance instructor, and choreographer for over 12 years.  Steve first started dancing in college and was teaching swing by his senior year.  Since then, he has studied with a wide range of companies and instructors  including Arthur Murray, the Bethesda Dance Studio, DVIDA, and the Ballroom Dance Company, where he completed the Instructor Certification Training Program in Ballroom, Swing, and Latin dances and competed at the Yuletide Ball winning first in all eight American Rhythm dances.  Salsa immediately became a passion for him in 2001 after taking a single salsa class at Excalibur in Chicago, IL.  In 2003, Steve joined Son In Motion, a salsa performance group based in Washington DC.  While on the team, Steve performed at numerous locations including the Puerto Rico, Los Angeles, Toronto, and Bermuda salsa congresses. In 2007, Steve launched Salsazon, Rendezvousâ€™s student salsa performance group, and Dynamix.</p>
<p>Steve was born in New York and grew up primarily in VA with his parents and sister.  He graduated cum laude from Virginia Tech in 1998 with an Industrial Engineering B.S. and a Business Minor. In 2006, Together with Barry Durand and Rachelle Schiffli, Steve opened Rendezvous Social Dance & Fitness Club in Rockville, MD.  He now resides outside Washington, D.C. and works full-time for Diamond Consultants, a premier business strategy and technology consulting firm.  </p>
<p>Fun Fact:  Steve studied martial arts and competed in the 2002 U.S. Tae Kwon Do Federation competition in Chicago where he won gold, silver, and bronze medals.</p>
